567
00:42:43,059 --> 00:42:44,993
這些日子不好過
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}These were hard times.{\r}

568
00:42:48,031 --> 00:42:51,728
我跟你說過我曾被閃電擊了7次嗎？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Did I ever tell you I was struck by lightning seven times?{\r}

569
00:42:52,669 --> 00:42:56,070
一次是在田里放牛
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Once when I was in the field, just tending to my cows.{\r}

570
00:43:02,612 --> 00:43:04,876
我的夥計沒來
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}My fourth hand didn't show up.{\r}

571
00:43:07,116 --> 00:43:10,574
有人想在這打工賺個2塊錢嗎？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Anybody want to make $2 for a day's work 'round here?{\r}

572
00:43:12,522 --> 00:43:14,217
怎麼了？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}What's the matter?{\r}

573
00:43:14,324 --> 00:43:17,054
沒人想勤懇工作賺這一天的工錢？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Nobody wants to do an honest day's work for an honest day's pay?{\r}

574
00:43:17,193 --> 00:43:18,717
他從不給錢
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}He never pays.{\r}

575
00:43:20,196 --> 00:43:22,494
- 沒人要做？ - 我做
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- Nobody wants a job? - I do.{\r}

576
00:43:24,133 --> 00:43:26,966
你不暈船吧 老頭？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}You got your sea legs about you, old man?{\r}

577
00:43:28,071 --> 00:43:29,436
我想是的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I think.{\r}

578
00:43:33,409 --> 00:43:35,843
很好 這就夠了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Well, that's good enough for me.{\r}

579
00:43:35,945 --> 00:43:39,403
快上船 上來就知道了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Get your ass on board. We'll sure as hell find out.{\r}

580
00:43:44,921 --> 00:43:46,548
我從沒這麼開心過
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I was as happy as I could be.{\r}

581
00:43:46,656 --> 00:43:47,918
誰來幫忙！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I need a volunteer!{\r}

582
00:43:48,024 --> 00:43:49,355
我什麼都做
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I would do anything.{\r}

583
00:43:49,459 --> 00:43:50,892
是 船長！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Yes, Captain!{\r}

584
00:43:50,994 --> 00:43:53,292
把鳥屎都刮了！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Scrape off all this bird shit!{\r}

585
00:43:54,030 --> 00:43:55,725
馬上 先生
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Right away, sir.{\r}

586
00:43:56,566 --> 00:44:01,026
事實上 本沒報酬的我卻拿到了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}And I was actually gonna be paid for something I would've done for free.{\r}

587
00:44:02,705 --> 00:44:05,037
他是邁克·克拉克船長
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}His name was Captain Mike Clark.{\r}

588
00:44:06,042 --> 00:44:08,943
7歲起就在拖船上了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}He'd been on a tugboat since he was seven.{\r}

589
00:44:09,979 --> 00:44:11,708
上來
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Get moving, then.{\r}

590
00:44:12,649 --> 00:44:14,139
過來
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Come here.{\r}

591
00:44:16,219 --> 00:44:19,313
你還能勃起嗎？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Can you still get it up?{\r}

592
00:44:20,690 --> 00:44:22,681
每天早上都行
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I do every morning.{\r}

593
00:44:23,359 --> 00:44:26,760
就憑這根 哈？能豎得老高老硬的？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}The old pole, huh? The high, hard one?{\r}

594
00:44:27,397 --> 00:44:28,694
我想是的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I guess.{\r}

595
00:44:31,300 --> 00:44:33,928
你上一次碰女人是什麼時候？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}When was the last time you had a woman?{\r}

596
00:44:36,472 --> 00:44:38,372
- 從沒碰過 - 從沒碰過？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- Never. - Never?{\r}

597
00:44:38,875 --> 00:44:40,934
我記得沒有 先生
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Not that I know of, sir.{\r}

598
00:44:41,444 --> 00:44:43,207
等等
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Wait a minute, now.{\r}

599
00:44:44,013 --> 00:44:48,143
你是說你活了這麼多年
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}You mean to say you've been on this earth however many years{\r}

600
00:44:48,251 --> 00:44:51,516
還沒上過女人？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}and you've never had a woman?{\r}

601
00:44:56,192 --> 00:44:59,252
見鬼 這是我聽過最慘的事了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Damn, that's the saddest thing I've ever heard in my life.{\r}

602
00:45:00,730 --> 00:45:01,958
從沒碰過？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Never?{\r}

603
00:45:02,732 --> 00:45:03,824
沒有
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}No.{\r}

604
00:45:06,469 --> 00:45:10,565
好吧 你得感謝老天爺讓你遇上我
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Well, then, by Jesus, you are coming with me.{\r}

605
00:45:21,584 --> 00:45:23,176
你父親做什麼的？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}What did your father do?{\r}

606
00:45:23,286 --> 00:45:25,311
我從沒見過我父親
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I never met my father.{\r}

607
00:45:25,421 --> 00:45:27,355
你這走運的雜種
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}You lucky bastard.{\r}

608
00:45:28,257 --> 00:45:30,885
做父親的都想壓制兒子
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}All fathers want to do is hold you down.{\r}

609
00:45:33,529 --> 00:45:36,930
我在我父親的船上日夜做工
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Out on my father's boat, workin' the two-a-day,{\r}

610
00:45:37,266 --> 00:45:39,700
這個混蛋胖子
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}this little, fat bastard.{\r}

611
00:45:39,802 --> 00:45:41,497
別人都叫他「愛爾蘭苦力」
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}"Tug Irish," they called him.{\r}

612
00:45:41,604 --> 00:45:44,971
不過最後我終於鼓足勇氣跟他說
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Anyway, I finally work up the nerve and tell him,{\r}

613
00:45:45,875 --> 00:45:49,572
「我不想把我的一輩子都浪費在這破船上」
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}"I don't want to spend the rest of my life on a goddamn tugboat."{\r}

614
00:45:49,679 --> 00:45:51,647
知道我的意思嗎？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}You know what I'm saying?{\r}

615
00:45:52,048 --> 00:45:54,710
你不想把一輩子浪費在破船上
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}You don't want to spend the rest of your life on a tugboat.{\r}

616
00:45:54,817 --> 00:45:57,115
對！就是這樣！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Absolutely! Damn right!{\r}

617
00:45:59,889 --> 00:46:02,483
那你知道我爸怎麼回答嗎？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}So you know what my father says to me?{\r}

618
00:46:03,326 --> 00:46:07,763
他說 「你他媽以為自己是誰？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}He says, "Who the hell do you think you are?{\r}

619
00:46:07,864 --> 00:46:10,594
「你他媽以為自己能做什麼？」
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}"What the hell do you think you can do?"{\r}

620
00:46:10,900 --> 00:46:12,561
然後我告訴他
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}So I tell him.{\r}

621
00:46:13,202 --> 00:46:16,399
「既然你問了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}"Well, if you're asking,{\r}

622
00:46:18,674 --> 00:46:20,699
「我想當藝術家」
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}"I want to be an artist."{\r}

623
00:46:21,277 --> 00:46:23,177
他笑了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}He laughs.{\r}

624
00:46:23,679 --> 00:46:28,673
「藝術家？你就是干拖船的命 就和我一樣"
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}"An artist? God meant for you to work a tugboat, just like me.{\r}

625
00:46:28,785 --> 00:46:31,413
「老老實實地給我幹活」
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}"And that's exactly what you're gonna do."{\r}

626
00:46:31,521 --> 00:46:34,752
後來我真成了藝術家
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Well, I turned myself into an artist.{\r}

627
00:46:37,226 --> 00:46:38,955
一個紋身藝術家！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}A tattoo artist!{\r}

628
00:46:41,397 --> 00:46:44,195
這都是我自己紋的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I put on every one of these myself.{\r}

629
00:46:46,736 --> 00:46:50,536
要拿走我的藝術 你得先活剝了我
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}You have to skin me alive to take my art away from me now.{\r}

630
00:46:51,340 --> 00:46:54,832
我死後 要把自己的手臂給他
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}When I'm dead, I'm gonna send him my arm.{\r}

631
00:46:56,112 --> 00:46:57,511
那條
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}That one.{\r}

632
00:46:59,849 --> 00:47:02,477
讓別人去說吧
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Don't let anyone tell you different.{\r}

633
00:47:02,585 --> 00:47:05,179
想做什麼就去做
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}You gotta do what you're meant to do.{\r}

634
00:47:05,288 --> 00:47:08,382
我碰巧就成了他媽的藝術家
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}And I happen to be a goddamned artist.{\r}

635
00:47:08,991 --> 00:47:11,289
可你還是個拖船船長
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}But you're a tugboat captain.{\r}

636
00:47:11,894 --> 00:47:13,623
邁克船長？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Captain Mike?{\r}

637
00:47:13,729 --> 00:47:16,459
我們已經為你和你的朋友準備好了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}We're ready for you and your friend.{\r}

638
00:47:18,201 --> 00:47:21,227
走吧 老傢伙 去破你的身吧
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Let's go, old timer, eh? Break your cherry.{\r}

639
00:47:22,438 --> 00:47:25,134
