641
00:47:28,411 --> 00:47:29,503
- 嗨 - 嗨
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- Hi. - Hi.{\r}

642
00:47:29,612 --> 00:47:32,638
好噁心 我才不要
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}He gives me the willies. That is not for me.{\r}

643
00:47:34,584 --> 00:47:36,848
今晚過得如何 老爺爺？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}How are you tonight, grandpa?{\r}

644
00:47:37,520 --> 00:47:39,647
那是一個難忘的夜晚
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}It was a night to remember.{\r}

645
00:47:45,394 --> 00:47:49,057
你是什麼 狄克·崔西還是什麼？ 我得休息休息 
（根據美國暢銷漫畫書改編拍攝的大型偵探片中的主角）
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}What are you, Dick Tracy or something? I've got to rest.{\r}

646
00:47:50,199 --> 00:47:51,427
再來
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Again.{\r}

647
00:47:52,735 --> 00:47:55,067
- 謝謝 - 不 該謝謝你 你今晚過得不錯
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- Thank you. - No, thank you. You have a nice night.{\r}

648
00:47:55,171 --> 00:47:57,298
- 明天你還在嗎？ - 除了星期天每天都在
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- Will you be here tomorrow? - Every night but Sunday.{\r}

649
00:47:57,406 --> 00:48:01,103
我想我明白了掙錢的重要
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}It sure made me understand the value of earning a living.{\r}

650
00:48:01,744 --> 00:48:03,575
晚安 寶貝 再來哦
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Good night, sweetie. Come back now.{\r}

651
00:48:03,679 --> 00:48:05,874
錢能買到一切
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Things money can buy you.{\r}

652
00:48:23,566 --> 00:48:25,227
外面髒
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}It's nasty out.{\r}

653
00:48:25,701 --> 00:48:28,602
要搭車嗎？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Can I offer you a ride somewhere?{\r}

654
00:48:30,373 --> 00:48:32,637
您真是太好了 先生
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Well, that's awfully kind of you, sir.{\r}

655
00:48:41,984 --> 00:48:44,452
我叫托馬斯 托馬斯·巴頓
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}My name is Thomas, Thomas Button.{\r}

656
00:48:45,121 --> 00:48:47,214
- 我叫本傑明 - 本傑明
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- I'm Benjamin. - Benjamin.{\r}

657
00:48:48,491 --> 00:48:50,618
很高興認識你
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}It's a pleasure to know you.{\r}

658
00:48:52,161 --> 00:48:55,392
願意停下去喝杯嗎？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Would you like to stop somewhere and have a drink?{\r}

659
00:48:55,498 --> 00:48:56,863
好啊
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}All right.{\r}

660
00:48:58,167 --> 00:49:00,431
晚上好 巴頓先生
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Evening, Mr. Button.{\r}

661
00:49:05,007 --> 00:49:06,941
要點什麼 先生？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}What'll it be, sir?{\r}

662
00:49:07,677 --> 00:49:10,703
- 跟他一樣 - 給我們都來薩澤拉克雞尾酒
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- I'll have whatever he's having. - Sazerac for the both of us.{\r}

663
00:49:10,813 --> 00:49:13,179
加威士忌 不要白蘭地
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}With whiskey, not brandy.{\r}

664
00:49:13,282 --> 00:49:14,772
你不喝酒？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}You don't drink, do you?{\r}

665
00:49:14,884 --> 00:49:17,478
- 今晚什麼都是第一次啊 - 怎麼說？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- It's a night for firsts. - How's that?{\r}

666
00:49:17,586 --> 00:49:19,645
以前從沒找過妓女
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I've never been to a brothel, either.{\r}

667
00:49:19,755 --> 00:49:22,519
這是種經歷
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Well, it's an experience.{\r}

668
00:49:22,658 --> 00:49:25,752
當然 凡事總有第一次
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}It certainly is. There's a time for everything.{\r}

669
00:49:25,861 --> 00:49:28,261
- 沒錯 - 你們的酒
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- True enough. - Your drinks.{\r}

670
00:49:29,932 --> 00:49:35,131
恕我冒昧 你的手 痛嗎？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I don't mean to be rude, but your hands. Is that painful?{\r}

671
00:49:35,471 --> 00:49:38,099
我生來就有些病
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Well, I was born with some form of disease.{\r}

672
00:49:38,207 --> 00:49:39,765
什麼病？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}What kind of disease?{\r}

673
00:49:39,875 --> 00:49:41,604
我天生就是老頭
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I was born old.{\r}

674
00:49:43,145 --> 00:49:44,840
- 抱歉 - 沒關係
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- I'm sorry. - No need to be.{\r}

675
00:49:44,947 --> 00:49:47,472
年老沒什麼錯
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}There's nothing wrong with old age.{\r}

676
00:49:56,359 --> 00:49:59,385
我妻子多年前去世了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}My wife passed away many years ago.{\r}

677
00:50:00,796 --> 00:50:02,627
非常抱歉
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I'm so, so sorry.{\r}

678
00:50:04,100 --> 00:50:05,965
難產死的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}She died in childbirth.{\r}

679
00:50:09,472 --> 00:50:11,997
- 敬孩子 - 敬母親
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- To children. - To mothers.{\r}

680
00:50:16,846 --> 00:50:19,110
你幹哪行的 巴頓先生？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}What line of work you in, Mr. Button?{\r}

681
00:50:19,215 --> 00:50:23,345
紐扣 巴頓紐扣公司 我們生產各類紐扣
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Buttons. Button's Buttons. There isn't a button that we don't make.{\r}

682
00:50:25,554 --> 00:50:27,920
我們最大的競爭對手是B.F.富善公司
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Our biggest competition is B.F. Goodrich{\r}

683
00:50:28,024 --> 00:50:29,753
還有他們該死的拉鏈
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}and his infernal zippers.{\r}

684
00:50:29,859 --> 00:50:32,657
先生們還要來點什麼嗎？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Would you gentlemen like anything else?{\r}

685
00:50:32,762 --> 00:50:34,787
再來杯上路 本傑明？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}One for the road, Benjamin?{\r}

686
00:50:34,897 --> 00:50:37,730
這次算我的 巴頓先生
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Only if you let me pay for it, Mr. Button.{\r}

687
00:50:39,001 --> 00:50:41,469
那你是幹哪行的？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}So, what line of work do you do?{\r}

688
00:50:42,905 --> 00:50:45,339
我是個拖船工人
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I'm a tugboat man.{\r}

689
00:50:51,547 --> 00:50:53,572
跟你聊天很開心
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I enjoyed talking to you.{\r}

690
00:50:54,050 --> 00:50:56,177
跟你喝酒也很開心
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I enjoyed drinking with you.{\r}

691
00:50:59,789 --> 00:51:01,188
本傑明？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Benjamin?{\r}

692
00:51:01,290 --> 00:51:04,726
我可以不時過來看看你嗎？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Would you mind if, time to time, I stopped by and said hello?{\r}

693
00:51:04,827 --> 00:51:08,228
隨時歡迎 晚安 巴頓先生
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Anytime. Good night, Mr. Button.{\r}

694
00:51:08,764 --> 00:51:10,527
晚安 本傑明
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Good night, Benjamin.{\r}

695
00:51:11,267 --> 00:51:12,632
開車
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Drive on.{\r}

696
00:51:18,307 --> 00:51:19,638
你去哪了？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Where have you been?{\r}

697
00:51:19,742 --> 00:51:24,736
沒什麼 遇到了個人 聽了會音樂
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Nothing. I met some people and listened to some music.{\r}

698
00:51:27,516 --> 00:51:29,711
哦 天啊 孩子！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Oh, sweet Jesus, boy!{\r}

699
00:51:30,719 --> 00:51:33,813
長大是件很有意思的事 不經意間就發生了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Growing up's a funny thing. Sneaks up on you.{\r}

700
00:51:34,757 --> 00:51:39,091
本來是這樣一個人 然後突然間變成了另一個人
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}One person is there, then suddenly somebody else has taken her place.{\r}

701
00:51:39,695 --> 00:51:41,356
不再是原來那樣子
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}She wasn't all elbows and knees anymore.{\r}

702
00:51:41,464 --> 00:51:43,159
本傑明！過來！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Benjamin! Come on!{\r}

703
00:51:43,532 --> 00:51:44,897
來了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Okay.{\r}

704
00:51:46,168 --> 00:51:47,726
我喜歡那些週末 她會來這
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I loved those weekends when she'd come{\r}

705
00:51:47,837 --> 00:51:50,635
和她的奶奶共度晚上
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}and spend the night with her grandmother.{\r}

706
00:51:58,714 --> 00:52:01,182
黛西 黛西
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Daisy. Daisy.{\r}

707
00:52:02,384 --> 00:52:04,511
給你看些東西？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}You want to see something?{\r}

708
00:52:05,688 --> 00:52:10,455
不過你得保密 快穿好衣服 我在外面等你
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}You gotta keep it a secret, so get dressed. I'll meet you out back.{\r}

709
00:52:15,998 --> 00:52:17,363
快點
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Come on.{\r}

710
00:52:19,168 --> 00:52:22,296
- 你會游泳嗎？ - 你會的我也會
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- Can you swim? - I can do anything you can do.{\r}

711
00:52:22,404 --> 00:52:24,998
給 穿上 我們得動作快點
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Here, put this on. We gotta hurry.{\r}

712
00:52:37,953 --> 00:52:39,477
他還好嗎？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Is he okay?{\r}

713
00:52:39,588 --> 00:52:41,021
船長？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Captain?{\r}

714
00:52:42,658 --> 00:52:44,148
邁克船長？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Captain Mike?{\r}

715
00:52:47,897 --> 00:52:50,593
早上好 船長 能帶我們出海嗎？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Morning, Captain. Can you take us out?{\r}

716
00:52:51,767 --> 00:52:54,065
知道今天星期幾嗎？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Do you know what day it is?{\r}

717
00:52:54,170 --> 00:52:55,432
星期天？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Sunday?{\r}

718
00:52:55,538 --> 00:52:57,665
知道那表示什麼嗎？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Do you know what that means?{\r}

719
00:52:59,008 --> 00:53:01,408
意味著我昨晚喝醉了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Means I was very drunk last night.{\r}

720
00:53:02,011 --> 00:53:04,275
你哪天不喝醉
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Well, you're drunk every night.{\r}

721
00:53:06,749 --> 00:53:09,013
- 是個女孩？ - 好朋友
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- Is that a girl? - Close friend.{\r}

722
00:53:09,752 --> 00:53:10,844
我想帶她看河
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I want to show her the river.{\r}

723
00:53:10,953 --> 00:53:14,252
你別偷偷帶外人出海
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}You're not supposed to go joyriding with civilians.{\r}

724
00:53:15,424 --> 00:53:17,551
我會丟掉執照的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I could lose my license.{\r}

725
00:53:27,369 --> 00:53:28,836
你還等什麼？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}What are you waiting for?{\r}

726
00:53:59,034 --> 00:54:02,128
要進站維修了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Pulled in for repair a wounded duck.{\r}

727
00:54:03,572 --> 00:54:05,699
她在飛了 哈？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}She's flying now, huh?{\r}

728
00:54:06,242 --> 00:54:07,869
喂 水手！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Ahoy, sailor!{\r}

729
00:54:12,448 --> 00:54:14,780
真希望能和他們一起去
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I wish we could go with them.{\r}

730
00:54:20,789 --> 00:54:23,053
你在說什麼 媽媽？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Did you say something, Mom?{\r}

731
00:54:30,833 --> 00:54:32,801
天氣越來越糟
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}It's getting really bad.{\r}

732
00:54:34,837 --> 00:54:36,600
能聽見嗎 媽媽？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Can you hear me, Mom?{\r}

733
00:54:39,241 --> 00:54:41,903
我沒多少時間了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Time just seeped out of me.{\r}

734
00:54:48,684 --> 00:54:50,481
「變化太快」
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}"Things were changing quickly."{\r}

735
00:54:50,586 --> 00:54:54,682
不知怎麼回事 可你的頭髮多了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I don't know how it's possible, but you seem to have more hair.{\r}

736
00:54:56,225 --> 00:54:59,194
要是我告訴你我沒有變老
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}What if I told you that I wasn't getting older,{\r}

737
00:54:59,295 --> 00:55:02,594
而是變得更年輕了呢？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}but I was getting younger than everybody else?{\r}

738
00:55:02,698 --> 00:55:06,600
那真不幸
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Well, I'd feel sorry for you,{\r}

739
00:55:06,702 --> 00:55:09,535
你必須看著你愛的人先你而去
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}to have to see everybody you love die before you do.{\r}

740
00:55:09,638 --> 00:55:11,538
真是可怕的責任
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}It's an awful responsibility.{\r}

741
00:55:11,640 --> 00:55:15,201
我以前從沒想過生死
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I'd never thought about life or death that way before.{\r}

742
00:55:16,845 --> 00:55:20,906
本傑明 我們命中注定要失去所愛之人
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Benjamin, we're meant to lose the people we love.{\r}

743
00:55:21,383 --> 00:55:24,750
不然我們怎麼知道 他們在我們生命中有多重要？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}How else would we know how important they are to us?{\r}

744
00:55:27,856 --> 00:55:32,316
秋天的一天 死神不期而至
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}And one fall day, a familiar visitor came knocking on our door.{\r}

745
00:55:34,063 --> 00:55:36,861
跟我一起去雜貨店嗎？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}You want to go with me to the drugstore?{\r}

746
00:55:47,009 --> 00:55:49,375
她教我彈鋼琴
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}She taught me how to play the piano.{\r}

747
00:55:49,478 --> 00:55:50,740
- 阿門 - 阿門
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- Amen. - Amen.{\r}

748
00:55:50,846 --> 00:55:54,009
她讓我明白了失去一個人的感覺
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}And she taught me what it meant to miss somebody.{\r}

749
00:55:58,587 --> 00:56:00,020
走吧
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Let's go.{\r}

750
00:56:01,056 --> 00:56:02,990
我去過妓院
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I had gone to a brothel.{\r}

751
00:56:03,092 --> 00:56:05,390
我喝過酒
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I'd had my first drink.{\r}

752
00:56:05,494 --> 00:56:08,952
跟一個朋友道別 跟另一個朋友永別
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Said goodbye to one friend and buried another.{\r}

753
00:56:09,498 --> 00:56:14,367
1936年我人生的第17個年末
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}In 1936, when I was coming to the end of the 17th year of my life,{\r}

754
00:56:14,470 --> 00:56:17,303
我收拾了行裝跟大家告別
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I packed my bag, said goodbye.{\r}

755
00:56:17,406 --> 00:56:19,738
- 再見 本傑明 - 再見
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- Bye, Benjamin. - Goodbye.{\r}

756
00:56:19,842 --> 00:56:24,302
我知道 生活仍將繼續 也許我再也見不到他們了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I knew, life being what it was, I'd probably never see them again.{\r}

757
00:56:26,515 --> 00:56:28,142
再見 本傑明先生
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Bye, Mr. Benjamin.{\r}

758
00:56:28,250 --> 00:56:30,718
- 祝你好運 兒子 - 謝謝
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- Good luck to you, son. - Thank you.{\r}

759
00:56:35,257 --> 00:56:38,158
- 我愛你 媽媽 - 我也愛你 寶貝
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- I love you, Mama. - I love you, too, baby.{\r}

760
00:56:39,361 --> 00:56:42,592
別忘了每晚做祈禱 好嗎？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I want you to say your prayers every night, hear?{\r}

761
00:56:47,469 --> 00:56:49,494
平平安安的 聽見了嗎？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Be safe, hear?{\r}

762
00:57:00,916 --> 00:57:02,281
本傑明！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Benjamin!{\r}

763
00:57:05,387 --> 00:57:08,015
- 你去哪？ - 出海
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- Where you going? - To sea.{\r}

764
00:57:09,425 --> 00:57:11,484
我會給你寄明信片的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I'll send you a postcard.{\r}

765
00:57:13,328 --> 00:57:15,262
無論在哪
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}From everywhere.{\r}

766
00:57:15,364 --> 00:57:17,958
無論在哪都要給我寄明信片
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Write me a postcard from everywhere.{\r}

767
00:57:32,481 --> 00:57:34,346
你能想像嗎？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Can you imagine?{\r}

768
00:57:36,752 --> 00:57:42,850
無論他去哪 在什麼地方工作
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}He sent me a postcard from everywhere he went.{\r}

769
00:57:44,426 --> 00:57:46,394
都會給我寄明信片
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Every place he worked.{\r}

770
00:57:47,729 --> 00:57:50,789
紐芬蘭 巴芬灣
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Newfoundland. Baffin Bay.{\r}

771
00:57:51,400 --> 00:57:54,460
格拉斯哥 利物浦 納爾維克
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Glasgow. Liverpool. Narvik.{\r}

772
00:57:55,270 --> 00:58:00,003
他和邁克船長一起去的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}He had gone with that Captain Mike.{\r}

773
00:58:02,044 --> 00:58:04,274
邁克船長和莫蘭兄弟拖船打撈公司
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Captain Mike had contracted for three years{\r}

774
00:58:04,379 --> 00:58:06,677
簽了3年的合約
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}with Moran Brothers Tug and Salvage.{\r}

775
00:58:06,782 --> 00:58:10,650
舊船裝上了柴油機和新的絞車
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}The old ship had been refitted with a diesel engine and a new sea winch.{\r}

776
00:58:10,752 --> 00:58:13,653
我們繞過了佛羅里達 沿著大西洋海岸北上
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}We went around Florida and up the Atlantic seaboard.{\r}

777
00:58:13,755 --> 00:58:17,156
船上現在有7名船員了 邁爾船長和我
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}We were a crew of seven now. Captain Mike and me.{\r}

778
00:58:17,259 --> 00:58:20,592
廚師 來自特拉華州威靈頓的普蘭提斯·梅斯
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Cookie, Prentiss Mayes from Wilmington, Delaware.{\r}

779
00:58:20,696 --> 00:58:23,096
布羅迪雙胞胎 塈J和維克
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}The Brody twins, Rick and Vic,{\r}

780
00:58:23,198 --> 00:58:25,428
在海上這兄弟倆相處很好 但不知什麼原因
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}who got along fine at sea but, for some reason,{\r}

781
00:58:25,534 --> 00:58:28,594
一旦回到陸地 他們就不對盤
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}once they were on dry land couldn't stand the sight of each other.{\r}

782
00:58:28,704 --> 00:58:32,265
你知道的 每八艘船就有一艘永遠回不來
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}You know, one in every eight boats never returns.{\r}

783
00:58:32,374 --> 00:58:34,501
一個叫約翰·格林的 人如其名
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}There was John Grimm, who sure fit his name.{\r}

784
00:58:34,610 --> 00:58:36,441
全體船員在海上失蹤了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}All hands lost at sea.{\r}

785
00:58:36,545 --> 00:58:38,775
來自南達科他州的貝爾維迪市
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}From Belvedere, South Dakota.{\r}

786
00:58:40,182 --> 00:58:43,015
還有來自北卡羅來納州阿什維爾的 普萊森特·柯蒂斯
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}And Pleasant Curtis from Asheville, Notch.{\r}

787
00:58:43,118 --> 00:58:46,281
從不跟人說話 除了他自己
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Never said a word to anyone, except himself.{\r}

788
00:58:48,690 --> 00:58:51,284
我經常給他寫信
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I wrote him constantly.{\r}

789
00:58:52,928 --> 00:58:57,922
我告訴他我受邀參加紐約市
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I told him I had been invited to audition in New York City{\r}

790
00:58:58,500 --> 00:59:01,162
一所美國芭蕾學校的面試
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}for the School of American Ballet.{\r}

791
00:59:01,270 --> 00:59:02,669
請留下
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Please stay.{\r}

792
00:59:02,771 --> 00:59:04,898
謝謝 謝謝
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Thank you. Thank you.{\r}

793
00:59:06,875 --> 00:59:08,137
你可以留下來
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}You can stay.{\r}

794
00:59:10,646 --> 00:59:13,706
可我在團堥瓣ㄔX名
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}But I was relegated to the corps.{\r}

795
00:59:14,049 --> 00:59:16,415
只不過是個跳舞的流浪者
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Another dancing gypsy.{\r}

796
00:59:20,722 --> 00:59:22,246
本傑明！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Benjamin!{\r}

797
00:59:22,891 --> 00:59:25,359
第一次見你時
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}How is it when you showed up{\r}

798
00:59:25,460 --> 00:59:29,328
你比那個系船柱大不了多少 還一隻腳踩進了棺材
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}you were no bigger than a bollard with one foot in the grave,{\r}

799
00:59:29,431 --> 00:59:33,629
而現在 是我喝多了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}but now, either I drink a hell of a lot more than I think I do,{\r}

800
00:59:34,903 --> 00:59:36,530
還是你長個了？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}or you sprouted?{\r}

801
00:59:37,439 --> 00:59:39,202
你有什麼秘密？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}What's your secret?{\r}

802
00:59:40,642 --> 00:59:42,200
船長
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Well, Captain,{\r}

803
00:59:44,012 --> 00:59:45,809
你確實喝多了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}you do drink a lot.{\r}

804
00:59:50,619 --> 00:59:54,885
我們住在一個小旅館 名字不錯 叫冬宮
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}We stayed in a small hotel with a grand name, The Winter Palace.{\r}

805
00:59:54,990 --> 00:59:57,754
你根本不知道自己在說什麼
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}You have no idea what you're talking about.{\r}

806
00:59:57,859 --> 01:00:01,317
蜂鳥不是一般的鳥類
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}The hummingbird is not just another bird.{\r}

807
01:00:02,064 --> 01:00:05,761
它的心率達到每分鐘1200下
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Its heart rate's 1,200 beats per minute.{\r}

808
01:00:07,536 --> 01:00:10,232
它的翅膀每秒扇動80次
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Its wings beat 80 times a second.{\r}

809
01:00:12,174 --> 01:00:15,166
要是讓它無法扇動翅膀
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}If you was to stop their wings from beating,{\r}

810
01:00:15,811 --> 01:00:18,644
不到10秒就會死掉
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}it would be dead in less than 10 seconds.{\r}

811
01:00:19,648 --> 01:00:22,310
這不是一般的鳥
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}This is no ordinary bird.{\r}

812
01:00:22,985 --> 01:00:25,078
簡直就是奇跡
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}This is a frickin' miracle.{\r}

813
01:00:28,256 --> 01:00:32,158
人們用影像慢放扇翅膀的動作
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}They slowed down their wings with moving pictures,{\r}

814
01:00:32,828 --> 01:00:35,023
知道他們看到了什麼？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}and you know what they saw?{\r}

815
01:00:35,530 --> 01:00:38,328
它們的翼尖像這樣運動
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Their wingtips are doing that.{\r}

816
01:00:42,371 --> 01:00:46,205
知道數字8有什麼數學含義嗎？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}You know what the figure eight is the mathematical symbol for?{\r}

817
01:00:49,211 --> 01:00:50,735
無窮
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Infinity.{\r}

818
01:00:50,846 --> 01:00:52,177
無窮！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Infinity!{\r}

819
01:00:55,684 --> 01:00:58,585
每個人 不論語言和膚色有何差異
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Everybody, no matter what differences they had,{\r}

820
01:00:58,687 --> 01:01:02,714
卻都有一個共同點
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}the languages, the color of their skin, had one thing in common.{\r}

821
01:01:03,659 --> 01:01:06,025
每晚都會喝醉
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}They were drunk every single night.{\r}

822
01:01:06,128 --> 01:01:07,652
三樓 謝謝
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Three, please.{\r}

823
01:01:07,763 --> 01:01:09,355
能等一下嗎 親愛的？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Could you hold, dear, for us, please?{\r}

824
01:01:09,464 --> 01:01:11,728
非常感謝 晚上好
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Thank you very much. Good evening.{\r}

825
01:01:11,833 --> 01:01:14,529
她叫伊麗莎白·艾伯特
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Her name was Elizabeth Abbott.{\r}

826
01:01:14,636 --> 01:01:17,935
她並不漂亮 很平凡
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}She was not beautiful. She was plain as paper.{\r}

827
01:01:18,040 --> 01:01:20,838
但在我看來她很美
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}But she was pretty as any picture to me.{\r}

828
01:01:22,144 --> 01:01:24,169
你在看什麼？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}What are you looking at?{\r}

829
01:01:26,415 --> 01:01:28,940
你該知道 我們有個長期協議
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}If you must know, we have a longstanding agreement{\r}

830
01:01:29,051 --> 01:01:30,416
不醉不歸
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}never to go to bed sober.{\r}

831
01:01:30,519 --> 01:01:32,919
- 對嗎 親愛的？ - 隨你怎麼說 親愛的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- Isn't that right, darling? - Whatever you say, darling.{\r}

832
01:01:33,021 --> 01:01:35,080
她丈夫是沃爾特·艾伯特
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Her husband was Walter Abbott.{\r}

833
01:01:35,190 --> 01:01:39,092
他是英國貿易代表團在摩爾曼斯克的首席部長
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}He was Chief Minister of the British Trade Mission in Murmansk,{\r}

834
01:01:39,194 --> 01:01:40,821
而且他還是個間諜
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}and he was a spy.{\r}

835
01:01:40,929 --> 01:01:43,796
- 親愛的 - 哦 謝謝 親愛的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- Darling. - Oh, thank you, my darling.{\r}

836
01:01:43,899 --> 01:01:45,924
- 鑰匙 親愛的 - 噢 對
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- Key, darling. - Oh, yes.{\r}

837
01:01:50,439 --> 01:01:53,465
我的一隻鞋跟斷了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I broke my heel off one of my shoes.{\r}

838
01:01:53,575 --> 01:01:57,170
我不習慣只穿襪子走路
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I'm not in the habit of walking about in my stocking feet.{\r}

839
01:02:01,583 --> 01:02:03,744
那堨掑悗靰
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}They were long days there.{\r}

840
01:02:11,259 --> 01:02:13,227
夜晚更加漫長
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}And even longer nights.{\r}

841
01:02:15,430 --> 01:02:18,991
有一個晚上 我輾轉難眠
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}One particular night, I was having trouble sleeping.{\r}

842
01:02:20,435 --> 01:02:21,959
抱歉
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I'm sorry.{\r}

843
01:02:23,839 --> 01:02:25,568
我睡不著
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I couldn't sleep.{\r}

844
01:02:38,487 --> 01:02:41,945
我要去泡些茶 你要嗎？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I was gonna make some tea. Would you like some?{\r}

845
01:02:42,858 --> 01:02:44,689
哦 不用了 謝謝
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Oh, no. Thank you.{\r}

846
01:03:22,531 --> 01:03:24,089
牛奶？還是蜂蜜？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Milk? Honey?{\r}

847
01:03:24,733 --> 01:03:26,667
一點蜂蜜 謝謝
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}A bit of honey, please.{\r}

848
01:03:27,202 --> 01:03:28,965
我希望你不介意蜂蜜埵頂a蠅
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I hope you like flies in your honey.{\r}

849
01:03:29,070 --> 01:03:30,731
哦 還是算了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Oh, perhaps not.{\r}

850
01:03:45,587 --> 01:03:49,819
哦 也許多浸一會會更好
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Oh, maybe better to let it steep a little.{\r}

851
01:03:50,826 --> 01:03:52,020
浸？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Steep?{\r}

852
01:03:52,394 --> 01:03:53,452
浸泡
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Soak.{\r}

853
01:03:53,728 --> 01:03:57,391
我不知道 我的意思是 泡茶就該這樣
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I don't know, I mean, there's a proper way of making tea.{\r}

854
01:03:57,499 --> 01:04:00,730
我家鄉那都喜歡喝熱茶
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Well, where I'm from, people just want it to be hot.{\r}

855
01:04:00,836 --> 01:04:02,929
這樣啊
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Well, quite right.{\r}

856
01:04:11,847 --> 01:04:14,247
- 現在你是海員 - 水手
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- Now, you're a seaman. - A sailor.{\r}

857
01:04:14,349 --> 01:04:17,079
希望你不要介意 我忍不住想問
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I hope you won't think me impolite, but I have to ask,{\r}

858
01:04:17,185 --> 01:04:19,312
作為一個水手你是不是有點老？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}aren't you a little old to be working on a boat?{\r}

859
