01:13:41,082 --> 01:13:43,380
我們每晚見面
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}We saw each other every night.{\r}

967
01:13:43,985 --> 01:13:46,283
總是在同一間屋子
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}We always used the same room.{\r}

968
01:13:48,256 --> 01:13:51,589
可每次都有不同的體驗
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}But each time seemed new and different.{\r}

969
01:13:52,994 --> 01:13:54,427
過來
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Come here.{\r}

970
01:14:01,903 --> 01:14:03,302
伊麗莎白
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Elizabeth.{\r}

971
01:14:04,672 --> 01:14:06,071
晚安
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Good night.{\r}

972
01:14:08,776 --> 01:14:10,403
直到有一個晚上
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Until one night.{\r}

973
01:14:47,682 --> 01:14:53,279
昨天 1941年12月7日
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Yesterday, December 7th, 1941,{\r}

974
01:14:53,387 --> 01:14:56,481
恥辱的一天…
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}a date which will live in infamy...{\r}

975
01:14:56,591 --> 01:15:00,721
這是一場會議 一場事關未來的政治性會議
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}It's a meeting, a policy meeting regarding your future,{\r}

976
01:15:01,662 --> 01:15:03,220
可能不止如此
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}possibly beyond.{\r}

977
01:15:04,632 --> 01:15:07,192
夥計們 計劃有變
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}There's been a change of plan, lads.{\r}

978
01:15:07,401 --> 01:15:09,995
你們或許知道 或許不知道
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}As you may or may not know,{\r}

979
01:15:10,104 --> 01:15:12,698
日本人昨天轟炸了珍珠港
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}the Japs bombed Pearl Harbor yesterday.{\r}

980
01:15:13,140 --> 01:15:16,598
富蘭克林·德拉諾·羅斯福 要求我們每個人盡到自己的職責
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Frank D. Roosevelt's asked each of us to do our part.{\r}

981
01:15:17,111 --> 01:15:21,207
切爾西號被美國海軍徵用
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}The Chelsea's been commissioned to serve in the United States Navy.{\r}

982
01:15:21,649 --> 01:15:24,914
負責維修 打撈和營救
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}To repair, to salvage, and to rescue.{\r}

983
01:15:26,454 --> 01:15:30,788
有誰不想打仗 現在說還來得及
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Anybody doesn't want to go to war, now is the time to say so.{\r}

984
01:15:30,892 --> 01:15:35,090
只要你踏上了那艘船 你就是海軍了 朋友
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Once you set foot on that boat, you're in the Navy, friend.{\r}

985
01:15:38,332 --> 01:15:41,358
我一直想和你談談 邁克
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Yeah, I've been meaning to talk with you, Mike.{\r}

986
01:15:41,469 --> 01:15:43,460
我老婆的情況不好
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}My wife's doing poorly.{\r}

987
01:15:43,571 --> 01:15:46,301
我希望能再見她一面
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I'd like to maybe see her one more time.{\r}

988
01:15:48,042 --> 01:15:51,842
你現在可以自由地回家了 梅斯先生
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}You're free to make your way home any way you can, Mr. Mayes.{\r}

989
01:15:57,485 --> 01:15:59,248
他走了誰做飯啊？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Well, if he's leaving, who's gonna cook?{\r}

990
01:15:59,353 --> 01:16:03,414
食物中毒是海上人員死亡的最主要原因之一
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Food poisoning's one of the leading causes of death at sea.{\r}

991
01:16:03,524 --> 01:16:05,890
僅次於安全裝備不足
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Right after inadequate safety equipment.{\r}

992
01:16:05,993 --> 01:16:08,621
我會做飯 船長 幹了一輩子了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I can cook, Captain. Been doing it all my life.{\r}

993
01:16:08,729 --> 01:16:13,132
我不知道 你也厭戰 本傑明
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I don't know. You're a little moody for war, Benjamin.{\r}

994
01:16:13,234 --> 01:16:15,202
管他呢？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}What the hell?{\r}

995
01:16:15,303 --> 01:16:19,637
想打倒小日本和匈奴人的都跟我走
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I'll take any man wants to kick the shite out of the Japs and the Huns.{\r}

996
01:16:21,042 --> 01:16:24,808
就這樣吧 收拾行裝 我們要上戰場了 先生們！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}That's it, pack your gear. We're going to war, gentlemen!{\r}

997
01:16:31,686 --> 01:16:33,449
她留了紙條
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}She had left a note.{\r}

998
01:16:34,822 --> 01:16:37,552
她寫道 「能遇到你真好」
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}She wrote, "It was nice to have met you."{\r}

999
01:16:38,326 --> 01:16:39,918
就這樣
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}And that was it.{\r}

1000
01:16:43,164 --> 01:16:46,224
戰爭和我們想像的不一樣
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}It wasn't the war any of us expected.{\r}

1001
01:16:46,334 --> 01:16:49,963
我們只是拖走破損的船 其實都是些廢銅爛鐵
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}We would just tow crippled ships, scraps of metal, really.{\r}

1002
01:16:50,571 --> 01:16:53,540
真有戰爭 我們也沒看到
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}If there was a war, we didn't see it.{\r}

1003
01:16:55,443 --> 01:16:59,504
派給我們的主炮手非常熱愛海軍
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}There was a man assigned to us. The Chief Gunner loved the Navy.{\r}

1004
01:16:59,614 --> 01:17:01,809
最重要的是他愛美國
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}But most of all, he loved America.{\r}

1005
01:17:01,916 --> 01:17:04,817
世界上沒有其他國家
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}There is no other country in the world.{\r}

1006
01:17:04,919 --> 01:17:06,011
當你拼寫美國…
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}When you spell America...{\r}

1007
01:17:06,120 --> 01:17:10,284
他叫丹尼斯·史密斯 是個純血統的切羅基人 （美洲土著人）
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}His name was Dennis Smith, and he was a full-blooded Cherokee.{\r}

1008
01:17:10,391 --> 01:17:13,485
他的家族在美洲居住了500多年
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}His family had been Americans for over 500 years.{\r}

1009
01:17:13,594 --> 01:17:18,122
去他們的和平主義者 說什麼不會憑良心打仗
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}These pacifists. They say they won't fight on conscience.{\r}

1010
01:17:18,232 --> 01:17:21,827
要是所有人都憑良心
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Now, where would be if everybody decided to act{\r}

1011
01:17:21,936 --> 01:17:25,895
- 那會怎麼樣？ - 冷靜點 長官？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- according to their conscience? - Keep it down, would you, Chief?{\r}

1012
01:17:42,123 --> 01:17:45,493
嘿 我觀察你很久了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Hey. I've been watching you.{\r}

1013
01:17:46,661 --> 01:17:48,458
你看上去值得信任
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}You seem trustworthy.{\r}

1014
01:17:50,264 --> 01:17:52,357
萬一我有什麼不測
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}If something happens to me,{\r}

1015
01:17:56,437 --> 01:17:58,997
你能答應把這個給我老婆嗎？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}could you see that this gets to my wife?{\r}

1016
01:17:59,106 --> 01:18:03,634
他把全部工錢都給了我 一分錢也沒花過
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}He'd given me all of his pay. Hadn't spent a dime of it.{\r}

1017
01:18:05,546 --> 01:18:08,811
我希望家人知道 我時刻掛念著他們
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I want my family to know I was thinking about them.{\r}

1018
01:18:13,587 --> 01:18:15,418
全體船員到甲板上！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}All hands on deck!{\r}

1019
01:18:17,925 --> 01:18:20,723
快起來 你們這群懶豬！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Get your asses up here, you lazy bastards!{\r}

1020
01:18:42,016 --> 01:18:44,211
戰爭終於還是來了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}The war had finally found us.{\r}

1021
01:18:46,921 --> 01:18:48,388
都別動！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}All stop!{\r}

1022
01:18:51,125 --> 01:18:53,116
普萊森特 轉下那燈
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Pleasant, man that light.{\r}

1023
01:19:01,001 --> 01:19:05,165
一艘載有1300人的運輸艦被魚雷擊沉
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}A transport carrying 1,300 men had been split by a torpedo.{\r}

1024
01:19:07,575 --> 01:19:09,839
我們是第一個趕到現場的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}We were first to arrive at the scene.{\r}

1025
01:19:09,944 --> 01:19:13,505
- 關掉引擎！ - 都別動！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- Cut the engines! - All stop!{\r}

1026
01:19:18,652 --> 01:19:20,552
四周只有我們的聲音
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}We were the only sound.{\r}

1027
01:19:34,502 --> 01:19:35,901
夥計們！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Fellas!{\r}

1028
01:19:45,880 --> 01:19:46,938
潛水艇！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Sub!{\r}

1029
01:19:51,752 --> 01:19:54,550
我們絕對跑不過他們
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}We sure as hell can't outrun them fuckers.{\r}

1030
01:19:56,290 --> 01:19:58,588
各就各位！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Battle stations!{\r}

1031
01:20:08,469 --> 01:20:09,458
謝謝 長官
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Thank you, Chief.{\r}

1032
01:20:11,772 --> 01:20:12,864
什麼？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}What?{\r}

1033
01:20:25,853 --> 01:20:27,650
是最後一個麼？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Is that the last one?{\r}

1034
01:21:49,050 --> 01:21:50,350
船長！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Captain!{\r}

1035
01:22:05,950 --> 01:22:08,550
狗日的把我的畫打爛了！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}They shot the hell out of my painting!{\r}

1036
01:22:09,850 --> 01:22:11,650
握著我的手
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Give me your other hand.{\r}

1037
01:22:17,050 --> 01:22:18,050
你會沒事的 船長
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}You'll be all right, Captain.{\r}

1038
01:22:18,250 --> 01:22:22,450
天使們在天堂 給你留了個好地方呢
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}They got a nice spot in Heaven waiting for you. Nice spot.{\r}

1039
01:22:24,050 --> 01:22:27,050
不順心的時候 你可以像瘋狗一樣發狂
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}You can be as mad as a mad dog at the way things went.{\r}

1040
01:22:30,050 --> 01:22:33,750
可以破口大罵 詛咒命運
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}You could swear, curse the Fates.{\r}

1041
01:22:36,050 --> 01:22:38,150
但到頭來
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}But when it comes to the end,{\r}

1042
01:22:40,350 --> 01:22:42,050
還是得放手
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}you have to let go.{\r}

1043
01:22:49,150 --> 01:22:50,350
船長？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Captain?{\r}

1044
01:23:11,150 --> 01:23:14,450
那天 1328人離開了人間
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Thirteen hundred and twenty eight men died that day.{\r}

1045
01:23:16,750 --> 01:23:20,050
我和切羅基人丹尼斯·史密斯道別
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I said my goodbyes to the Cherokee, Dennis Smith.{\r}

1046
01:23:20,950 --> 01:23:24,150
和約翰·格林道別--他猜得沒錯 他最後還是死在那兒了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}John Grimm, who was right, he was gonna die there.{\r}

1047
01:23:25,750 --> 01:23:28,350
我把普萊森特·柯蒂斯的錢 寄給了他妻子
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I sent Pleasant Curtis' wife his money.{\r}

1048
01:23:29,250 --> 01:23:32,350
我向雙胞胎的維克·布羅迪道別
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I said goodbye to the twin, Vic Brody,{\r}

1049
01:23:32,450 --> 01:23:37,050
還有邁克·克拉克--切爾西號的船長
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}and to Mike Clark, captain of the tugboat Chelsea.{\r}

1050
01:23:39,550 --> 01:23:44,050
我和那些仍舊懷揣夢想的人道別
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I said goodbye to all the other men who had dreams of their own,{\r}

1051
01:23:44,150 --> 01:23:46,650
他們有的想做保險推銷員
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}all the men who wanted to be insurance salesmen{\r}

1052
01:23:46,750 --> 01:23:49,750
有的想當醫生 律師 甚至是部落酋長
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}or doctors or lawyers or Indian chiefs.{\r}

1053
01:23:50,750 --> 01:23:52,550
這個修不好了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}This don't get fixed.{\r}

1054
01:23:54,650 --> 01:23:57,750
在那兒 死亡不再是自然發生的了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Out here, death didn't seem natural.{\r}

1055
01:24:14,750 --> 01:24:17,950
我從沒在遠海上見過蜂鳥
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I'd never seen a hummingbird that far out to sea.{\r}

1056
01:24:19,450 --> 01:24:21,050
無論是之前 還是此後
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Before or since.{\r}

1057
01:24:26,850 --> 01:24:33,050
1945年5月 我26歲
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}And in May of 1945, when I was 26 years old,{\r}

1058
01:24:33,450 --> 01:24:34,550
我回家了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I came home.{\r}

1059
01:24:35,450 --> 01:24:38,050
我準備好了！準備好了！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I'm ready! I'm ready!{\r}

1060
01:24:38,150 --> 01:24:39,550
來了！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I'm coming!{\r}

1061
01:24:40,450 --> 01:24:44,050
- 我準備好了！ - 這就來了 阿法莉娜
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- I'm ready! - All right, I'm coming, Miss Alfalina.{\r}

1062
01:24:44,150 --> 01:24:45,650
- 奎尼？ - 嗯？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- Queenie? - Yes?{\r}

1063
01:24:51,550 --> 01:24:57,450
老天爺！你回來了！ 神啊 你回來了！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Sweet Jesus! Oh, you're home! Oh, Lord, you came back!{\r}

1064
01:24:58,350 --> 01:25:00,350
- 快讓我瞧瞧 - 他是誰呀 媽媽？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- Let me look at you. - Who's that, Mama?{\r}

1065
01:25:00,450 --> 01:25:03,650
- 孩子啊 這是你哥哥 本傑明 - 我都不知道我還有哥哥
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- Child, it's your brother, Benjamin. - I didn't know he was my brother.{\r}

1066
01:25:03,750 --> 01:25:05,450
你不知道的事情多了去了 小丫頭
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}There's a shitload of things you don't know, child.{\r}

1067
01:25:05,550 --> 01:25:06,750
趕緊去把地掃完
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Get on out there and finish sweeping.{\r}

1068
01:25:06,850 --> 01:25:08,950
再把手洗洗來幫我擺餐桌 快去
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Come here, wash your hands, help me with the table. Go on, now.{\r}

1069
01:25:09,050 --> 01:25:12,950
轉過來 你看起來跟重生了一樣！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Turn around. You look like you've been born again.{\r}

1070
01:25:13,050 --> 01:25:15,350
比春天還有活力！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Younger than the springtime.{\r}

1071
01:25:15,450 --> 01:25:19,050
要我說 那牧師施法的時候 肯定是又給了你一條命
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I think that preacher laid hands on you gave you a second life.{\r}

1072
01:25:19,150 --> 01:25:22,850
那會我看著你就知道 你跟別人不一樣
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I knew it that moment I saw you, you were special.{\r}

1073
01:25:22,950 --> 01:25:24,750
知道嘛 我的膝蓋現在都酸
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I tell you what, my knees are sore,{\r}

1074
01:25:24,950 --> 01:25:27,450
因為我每天晚上都跪著 求上帝保佑
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}'cause I've been on them every night asking the Lord,{\r}

1075
01:25:27,550 --> 01:25:31,250
求他「上帝啊 我只要他平安回家」
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I said, "God, just bring him home safely."{\r}

1076
01:25:31,350 --> 01:25:33,850
還記得我怎麼跟你說的嗎？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Remember what I told you?{\r}

1077
01:25:33,950 --> 01:25:35,650
「你永遠都猜不到 以後的生活是啥樣子」
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}"You never know what's coming for you"?{\r}

1078
01:25:35,750 --> 01:25:37,650
沒錯 快坐下
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}That's right. Sit down.{\r}

1079
01:25:39,050 --> 01:25:43,150
這幾年 有碰上什麼有趣兒的事嗎？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Well, you learn anything worth repeating?{\r}

1080
01:25:45,250 --> 01:25:49,450
- 當然了 - 你嘗過了苦頭
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- I sure saw some things. - Oh, you seen some pain.{\r}

1081
01:25:50,950 --> 01:25:53,750
- 也嘗過甜頭？ - 嗯
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- Some joy, too? - Sure. Sure, I did.{\r}

1082
01:25:53,850 --> 01:25:57,950
我就是想聽你親口說這些 瞧瞧你呀
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Yeah, that's what I want to hear. Look at you.{\r}

1083
01:25:58,050 --> 01:26:01,550
- 蒂奇上哪兒去了？ - 哦 孩子
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- Where's Tizzy? - Oh, baby.{\r}

1084
01:26:04,050 --> 01:26:07,950
韋瑟斯走了 上個月 睡覺的時候去的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Mr. Weathers died in his sleep one night last April.{\r}

1085
01:26:08,050 --> 01:26:11,450
- 媽媽 您節哀 - 別操心我了 孩子
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- Mama, I'm so sorry. - Don't you worry about that, baby.{\r}

1086
01:26:13,250 --> 01:26:15,850
現在還活著的也就那麼一兩個
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Yeah, well, it's only one or two of them left now.{\r}

1087
01:26:15,950 --> 01:26:17,450
不過都還挺樂呵
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}They all just about new.{\r}

1088
01:26:17,550 --> 01:26:21,450
他們應該和別人一樣 也都在等著那一天吧
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Guess they're waiting their turn like everybody else, huh?{\r}

1089
01:26:21,550 --> 01:26:24,250
你能回家陪我 我就知足了！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I'm so glad you're back home with me!{\r}

1090
01:26:24,350 --> 01:26:27,450
咱得趕緊給你找個媳婦 再找個工作 就這麼定了！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Now, we're gonna have to find you a wife and a new job! That's right.{\r}

1091
01:26:27,550 --> 01:26:29,450
快進來 幫我擺桌子
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Come on in here, help me with this table.{\r}

1092
01:26:32,650 --> 01:26:34,250
本傑明
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Benjamin.{\r}

1093
01:26:34,350 --> 01:26:37,450
別費勁了 她全聾了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}You're wasting your time, baby. She's stone deaf.{\r}

1094
01:26:37,550 --> 01:26:41,650
你住以前德瑟羅住的房間
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Oh, and you'll be staying in what was Mrs. DeSeroux's old room.{\r}

1095
01:26:41,750 --> 01:26:44,650
你太大個了 再和別人擠一間可不像話
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}You're too big to be rooming with anybody else.{\r}

1096
01:26:48,750 --> 01:26:51,350
回家的感覺 很奇妙
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}It's a funny thing about coming home.{\r}

1097
01:26:52,050 --> 01:26:55,750
一切看起來都是一樣的 聞起來也是 摸起來也是
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Looks the same, smells the same, feels the same.{\r}

1098
01:26:58,550 --> 01:27:02,350
我說沒說過 我被閃電擊中過七次？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Did I ever tell you I've been struck by lightning seven times?{\r}

1099
01:27:04,050 --> 01:27:07,450
有一次我就那麼好端端地開著車 心媟Q著自己的事
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Once when I was sitting in my truck, just minding my own business.{\r}

1100
01:27:13,350 --> 01:27:16,750
我才意識到 其實變的 只有你自己
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}You realize what's changed is you.{\r}

1101
01:27:19,450 --> 01:27:23,450
我回來後不久的某個清晨…
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}And late one morning, not long after I'd been back...{\r}

1102
01:27:23,850 --> 01:27:25,150
謝謝
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Thank you.{\r}

1103
01:27:47,250 --> 01:27:48,350
嘿
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Hey.{\r}

1104
01:27:52,950 --> 01:27:56,750
- 請問 奎尼在嗎？ - 黛西？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- Excuse me, is Queenie here? - Daisy?{\r}

1105
01:28:00,550 --> 01:28:04,150
- 是我啊 本傑明 - 本傑明？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- It's me, Benjamin. - Benjamin?{\r}

1106
01:28:07,850 --> 01:28:09,850
哦 天！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Oh, my God!{\r}

1107
01:28:11,150 --> 01:28:15,050
真的是你！本傑明！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Of course it's you! Benjamin!{\r}

1108
01:28:17,150 --> 01:28:20,050
你過得怎麼樣？ 咱們太久沒見了！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}How are you? It's been such a long time.{\r}

1109
01:28:20,150 --> 01:28:22,850
我有好多事情要問你 你什麼時候回來的？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}There's so much I want to know. When did you get back?{\r}

1110
01:28:22,950 --> 01:28:24,350
我回來也沒幾周
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Well, I got back a few weeks ago.{\r}

1111
01:28:24,450 --> 01:28:28,450
我上次問奎尼 她說你還在打仗 說是在海上的哪兒
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I spoke to Queenie, she said you were in the war, somewhere at sea.{\r}

1112
01:28:28,550 --> 01:28:32,350
- 我們都擔心死你了 - 哦 我挺好的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- We were so, so worried about you. - Oh, I'm okay.{\r}

1113
01:28:32,450 --> 01:28:36,250
瞧瞧你啊 真是好看
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Well, look at you. You're so lovely.{\r}

1114
01:28:38,050 --> 01:28:39,850
你後來就不給我寫信了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}You stopped writing.{\r}

1115
01:28:41,950 --> 01:28:47,050
「我離開的時候 她還只是個小女孩 如今 卻已出落成了窈窕淑女」
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}"When I had left, she was a girl. And a woman had taken her place.{\r}

1116
01:28:47,450 --> 01:28:50,550
「她是我所見過的人中 最美的女子」
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}"She was the most beautiful woman I'd ever seen."{\r}

1117
01:28:50,650 --> 01:28:52,050
美
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Beautiful.{\r}

1118
01:28:54,250 --> 01:28:56,050
是「最美」
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}"The most beautiful."{\r}

1119
01:28:57,850 --> 01:28:59,550
- 你還記得富勒奶奶嗎？ - 當然了 怎麼了？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- You remember Grandma Fuller? - Why, sure I do.{\r}

1120
01:28:59,650 --> 01:29:02,750
- 她過世了 - 我聽說了 節哀
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- She passed. - I heard that. I'm sorry.{\r}

1121
01:29:02,850 --> 01:29:07,450
真不敢想 我們又見面了 這一定是緣分
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I just can't believe we're both here. Must be fate.{\r}

1122
01:29:07,550 --> 01:29:09,450
不對不對 他們管這叫什麼來著？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}No, no, what do they call it?{\r}

1123
01:29:09,550 --> 01:29:10,950
天意
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Kismet.{\r}

1124
01:29:11,050 --> 01:29:12,950
你知道埃德加·西嗎？ 就是那個會通靈的？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Do you know about Edgar Cayce, the psychic?{\r}

1125
01:29:13,050 --> 01:29:14,050
應該沒…
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I don't believe I...{\r}

1126
01:29:14,150 --> 01:29:17,050
他說 萬事萬物都是注定的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}He says that everything is predetermined,{\r}

1127
01:29:17,150 --> 01:29:20,550
不過我寧願把這當成緣分
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}but I like to think of it as fate.{\r}

1128
01:29:23,750 --> 01:29:26,950
雖然也搞不懂這到底是怎麼回事 我還是很高興咱們重逢了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I'm not sure how it works, but I'm glad it happened.{\r}

1129
01:29:27,050 --> 01:29:30,650
你去過曼哈頓嗎？ 就在我住的地方河對面
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Have you been to Manhattan? It's right across the river from me.{\r}

1130
01:29:30,750 --> 01:29:32,950
要是我站在床上
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Now, I can see the Empire State Building{\r}

1131
01:29:33,050 --> 01:29:34,750
就可以望見帝國大廈
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}if I stand on my bed.{\r}

1132
01:29:34,850 --> 01:29:36,850
說說你吧？你都去哪了？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}What about you? Where have you been?{\r}

1133
01:29:36,950 --> 01:29:40,550
全都告訴我 上次你寫信說 你去俄國了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Tell me everything. Last time you wrote, you said you'd been to Russia.{\r}

1134
01:29:40,650 --> 01:29:44,850
我一直想去那呢 那兒真像別人說的那麼冷嗎？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I've always wanted to go to Russia. Is it as cold as they say?{\r}

1135
01:29:44,950 --> 01:29:47,750
- 冷多了 - 我的天呀
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}- Twice as cold. - My goodness.{\r}

1136
01:29:48,350 --> 01:29:52,950
大家嘴上都說你不一樣 我可是真的覺得你不是一般人
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}We always said you were different. But I think you really are.{\r}

1137
01:29:55,150 --> 01:29:58,650
你還說你遇上了你喜歡的人 最後有結果嗎？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}You wrote that you met somebody. Did it work out?{\r}

1138
01:29:59,150 --> 01:30:00,850
還是沒成
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}It ran its course.{\r}

1139
01:30:02,150 --> 01:30:04,250
嘿 還記得這個嗎？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Hey, do you remember this?{\r}

1140
01:30:15,150 --> 01:30:17,850
「照片媯e的是大袋鼠
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}"This is the picture of Old Man Kangaroo{\r}

1141
01:30:17,950 --> 01:30:20,050
下午五點 他終於會蹦蹦跳了」
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}"at 5:00 in the afternoon."{\r}

1142
01:30:21,850 --> 01:30:24,050
一起吃個晚飯好嗎？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Would you like to have dinner?{\r}

1143
01:30:31,550 --> 01:30:34,450
我有沒有跟你說過 我跟著巴蘭欽跳舞呀？ （著名芭蕾舞導演）
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Did I tell you that I danced for Balanchine?{\r}

1144
01:30:35,150 --> 01:30:39,650
他可是個有名的編舞大師 他說我的線條很完美
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Oh, he's a famous choreographer. He said that I had perfect line.{\r}

1145
01:30:41,450 --> 01:30:45,950
知道嗎 有一個排練 有人摔倒
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}You know, in a rehearsal once, a dancer fell.{\r}

1146
01:30:46,050 --> 01:30:48,850
然後他…就把這個動作 編進舞蹈堨h了！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}And he just... He just put it right into the production.{\r}

1147
01:30:48,950 --> 01:30:52,450
你能想像那情形嗎？ 在一部…經典芭蕾舞劇
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I mean, can you imagine that? Like in a... In a classical ballet?{\r}

1148
01:30:52,550 --> 01:30:55,750
讓一個演員 故意跌倒
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}You know, a dancer, intentionally falling.{\r}

1149
01:30:55,850 --> 01:30:59,550
如今形容舞蹈有個新詞了 叫「抽像」
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}There's a whole new word for dance now. It's called "abstract."{\r}

1150
01:30:59,650 --> 01:31:00,950
當然了 有名的大師不止他一個
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}No, he's not the only one, though.{\r}

1151
01:31:01,050 --> 01:31:04,950
還有林肯·柯爾斯坦 露西亞·切斯 哦 對…
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}There's Lincoln Kirstein and Lucia Chase, and oh, my...{\r}

1152
01:31:05,050 --> 01:31:07,550
還有阿格尼·德·米爾
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Oh, there's Agnes de Mille.{\r}

1153
01:31:07,650 --> 01:31:09,750
她根本就不管什麼條條框框
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}She's just torn up all those conventions,{\r}

1154
01:31:09,850 --> 01:31:11,850
就是「抬頭挺胸」那一套
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}you know, all that straight-up-and-down stuff.{\r}

1155
01:31:11,950 --> 01:31:15,150
她說舞蹈最重要的不是形式 而是舞者的感覺
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}It's not about the formality of the dance, it's about what the dancer's feeling.{\r}

1156
01:31:15,250 --> 01:31:17,950
她跟我說的這些 就像是另一個全新的世界
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}As she told me about this big new world,{\r}

1157
01:31:18,050 --> 01:31:20,550
那些名字 對我來說 啥也不是
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}names that didn't mean a thing to me,{\r}

1158
01:31:20,650 --> 01:31:22,650
其實她說什麼 我也沒怎麼聽進去
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I didn't really hear very much of what she was saying.{\r}

1159
01:31:22,750 --> 01:31:25,050
一切都是全新的 現代的 美式的！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}It's new and it's modern and it's American.{\r}

1160
01:31:25,150 --> 01:31:28,250
只有他們瞭解我們的活力和形體
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}They understand our vigor and our physicality.{\r}

1161
01:31:28,350 --> 01:31:30,550
哦 天 我是不是說太多了呀
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}Oh, my God. I've just been talking and talking.{\r}

1162
01:31:30,750 --> 01:31:35,150
沒有沒有 我喜歡聽你講 我不知道你還抽煙
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}No, no, I've enjoyed listening. I didn't know you smoked.{\r}

1163
01:31:35,250 --> 01:31:36,750
我夠大了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I'm old enough.{\r}

1164
01:31:40,150 --> 01:31:42,650
除了這個 還能做很多別的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H80FFFF&\3c&HFF0000&}I'm old enough for a lot of things.{\r}

1165
